      <description>&lt;figure style=&#34;padding: 0.25rem; margin: 2rem 0; background-color: #cccc&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img style=&#34;max-width: 100%; width: auto; height: auto;&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/mason-stains-staining-masonary/slips_underglazes.jpg&#34; width=&#34;3539&#34; height=&#34;2831&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;        &lt;small&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;                &#xD;&#xA;sample jars of coloured slips&#xD;&#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;        &lt;/small&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-internet-is-confusing&#34;&gt;The internet is confusing&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I spend a lot of time on the internet. On pottery forums I saw people talking about something called Mason stains, things that they seemed to be using to colour clay.&#xA;I swear, in every thread someone would pop up and say &amp;ldquo;my community studio doesn&amp;rsquo;t let us use Mason stains, what else can I use?&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
