      <description>&lt;figure style=&#34;padding: 0.25rem; margin: 2rem 0; background-color: #cccc&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img style=&#34;max-width: 100%; width: auto; height: auto;&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/porcelain-reclaim-what-the-hell-did-i-do/20250126_porcelain_reclaim_crack.jpg&#34; width=&#34;2304&#34; height=&#34;2826&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;        &lt;small&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;                &#xA;torn porcelain reclaim&#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;        &lt;/small&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;uh-oh&#34;&gt;uh-oh&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A huge crack all around the bottom of my wedging spiral, the clay just split open like rising sourdough, that&amp;rsquo;s what happened the first time I reclaimed porcelain.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Not exactly what I wanted to see, and it reminded me of my instructor talking about a friend who never reclaimed their porcelain. Had I just destroyed 4kg of clay?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
